(firstQuint)A Study to Evaluate Add on Effect of Solifenacin in Men With Overactive Bladder Symptoms After Tamsulosin Monotherapy for 4 Weeks.

 This is a multi-center study to evaluate the efficacy, safety, and persistency of solifenacin treatment in male patients with persistent OAB symptoms of urinary frequency and urgency with/without urgency incontinence who are receiving tamsulosin monotherapy for LUTS at a stable dose for 4 weeks in real life practice.

 Also proportion of patients and predictive factors with persistent OAB symptoms after tamsulosin monotherapy will be investigated.

